    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-13T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-13T20:00:00-05:00" n="57"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d57">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.96/332</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-13T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>957. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1">Chadbourne</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 4. Embassy’s 1124, March 9, 11 a.m. United States of course claims
                    jurisdiction of boats Canal Zone. Ordinarily exercised by this Board where
                    bunkers or supplies requested or Trading with the Enemy Act involved, but our
                    jurisdiction might be invoked respecting cargoes if needed by United States. Do
                    not understand what you mean by your question, “What must owners do?”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
